This paper deals with inverse kinematics for redundant structures, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the handling of constraints, which is a common topic in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization tasks and gradient descent is also mentioned, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
